### Step 5: Implement Accessibility

Canvas Kit handles most accessibility, but ensure:

#### Keyboard Navigation
- All interactive elements are keyboard accessible
- Tab order is logical
- Focus indicators are visible

#### ARIA Attributes
- Use semantic HTML when possible
- Add ARIA labels for non-obvious elements
- Ensure screen reader announcements are clear

#### Focus Management
- Modal focus traps work correctly
- Focus returns to trigger element after close
- Skip links for long content

#### Color Contrast
- Verify WCAG AA compliance (4.5:1 for normal text, 3:1 for large text)
- Use Canvas Kit tokens (they're already compliant)

**Example with accessibility**:
```tsx
<TextInput
  label="Email address"
  placeholder="you@example.com"
  required
  aria-required="true"
  aria-describedby="email-help"
/>
<span id="email-help" style={{ fontSize: '12px', color: colors.blackPepper400 }}>
  Enter your work email address
</span>
```

